NBBF President, Kida, Promises To Adequately Prepare Team For Tourney LAGOS – The draws for the 2022 FIBA Women’s World Cup held on Thursday in Australia with Nigeria’s D’Tigress tipping off their campaign against Japan on 22 September 2022. The FIBA Women’s Basketball World Cup 2022 will tip off on September 22 at Sydney Olympic Park. Nigeria D’Tigress Drawn In World Cup Group B D’Tigress Beat France, Keep World Cup Qualification Hopes Alive The Nigerian Ladies drawn in Group B of the World Cup against France, Serbia, Japan, Canada and Australia, will play their second game against host Australia on 23 September before playing France in their third game. D’Tigress will observe a day of rest before playing Serbia on 26 September 2022 with their last group game against Canada holding on 27 September 2022. Teams drawn in Group A are Belgium, China, Bosnia Herzegovina, Korea and the USA. FIBA Central Board will decide on the team that will replace Russia in Group A. Russia has been provisionally suspended indefinitely by FIBA following its invasion of Ukraine. Meanwhile, president of the Nigeria Basketball Federation Engr Musa Kida has expressed optimism that D’Tigress would make Nigeria proud in Sydney. Kida in his reaction to the draw, said D’Tigress have all the potential to emerge the best in the tournament, saying that the Federation would leave no stone unturned to ensure that they get the best of preparations before the World Cup tips off in Australia. POLL According to him, “we will do our best to ensure D’Tigress have a better preparation for the tournament, the team has been making the continent proud, I can assure that the forthcoming World Cup will be another avenue for the team to make Nigerians and Africa proud the more.” He, however, sought for the support of all stakeholders to move the game forward in the country.Recently, at the playoff in Serbia last month, D’Tigress beat France and Mali to qualify for the World Cup.